SUMMARY:Black Light Painting for Tweens
DESCRIPTION:Wear your brightest outfit (and maybe a smock) and watch it glow at this art program for middle grade youth! Participants will be painting canvases with neon paint by the groovy glow of our black lights. Come create a luminous work of art with your peers and get a free black light bulb to enjoy your art at home! \nDesigned for 6th to 8th graders. This event is free\, but registration is required\, as the program is limited to eight participants. For more information\, email loteen@lakeoswego.city(link sends e-mail) or contact the Information Desk at 503-697-6580. \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
